    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>παιδεύω[a] and παιδεία[a] ({D:33.226}) differ in meaning from νουθετέω[a] and νουθεσία[a] ({D:33.231}) and from ἐντρέφω ({D:33.242}). παιδεύω[a] and παιδεία[a] focus upon the forming of proper habits of behavior, while νουθετέω[a] and νουθεσία[a] focus upon instruction in correct behavior. ἐντρέφω appears to focus more on continuous instruction and training in the areas of skill and practical knowledge.</Content>
    </Note>
